        "Name" : "M.A.S.C. (Light)",
        "Details" : "Myomer Accelerator Signal Circuitry (MASC) is a piece of equipment that allows a BattleMech to move at twice its walking speed. However, actuators were not built for this kind of stress, and prolonged usage of MASC systems can damage the leg actuators of a BattleMech. Although this is unlikely to immobilize the BattleMech, the danger of destroyed actuators is enough for cautious warriors to limit their use in battle.\r\nMASC is incompatible with Triple Strength Myomer.\r\n\r\nThis variant can be used on Mechs between 25 and 40 tons.\r\n\r\n<b>Effect:</b>\r\n<color=#ffcc00>2x movement speed during activation.\r\n3% chance to fail on first activation, +19% flat chance to fail for every consecutive turn MASC is active (modified by piloting skill)\r\nAdditional 5% chance to fail per each activation after the first\r\n\r\nWhen MASC fails, both legs receive 10 points of damage.</color>\r\n\r\n<color=#d9d9d9><b>Activation state can be toggled by ctrl-clicking the move button in the HUD.</b></color>",
